<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML List Tags Example</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>1. Courses List (Ordered List)</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>Frontend Development
            <ul>
                <li>HTML Basics</li>
                <li>CSS Styling</li>
                <li>JavaScript Basics</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li>Backend Development
            <ul>
                <li>Node.js</li>
                <li>Express.js</li>
                <li>Database (MongoDB)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li>Design Tools
            <ul>
                <li>Photoshop</li>
                <li>Figma</li>
                <li>Canva</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <hr>

    <h1>2. Technologies (Unordered List)</h1>

    <ul>
        <li>Web Development
            <ol>
                <li>HTML Structure</li>
                <li>CSS Styling</li>
                <li>JavaScript Logic</li>
            </ol>
        </li>

        <li>Mobile Development
            <ol>
                <li>Android</li>
                <li>Flutter</li>
                <li>React Native</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <hr>

    <h1>3. Description List Example</h1>

    <dl>
        <dt>HTML</dt>
        <dd>Used to create structure of web pages</dd>

        <dt>CSS</dt>
        <dd>Used to design and style web pages</dd>

        <dt>JavaScript</dt>
        <dd>Used to add interactivity to web pages</dd>
    </dl>

    <hr>

    <h1>4. Full Nested Mixed Example</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>Programming Languages
            <ul>
                <li>Frontend
                    <ul>
                        <li>HTML</li>
                        <li>CSS</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>

                <li>Backend
                    <ul>
                        <li>Node.js</li>
                        <li>Python</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li>Tools</li>

        <dl>
            <dt>Git</dt>
            <dd>Version control system</dd>

            <dt>VS Code</dt>
            <dd>Code editor for development</dd>
        </dl>
    </ol>

</body>
</html>
